  "text": ". Earlier researchers also observed similar findings in the total phenolic content of different crops [CITATION_1] . Although in a previous study green peppers were found to have the highest activity in the phenolic extracts among three colored peppers [CITATION_2] , cultivar Odysseo in our experiments showed increased phenols in the red peppers rather than in the green, indicating a genotypic difference.",
